channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: REPORT: Michelle Obama Frustrated With Biden Family, How They Barred Her Friend and Hunter's Ex-Wife
Supreme Court rules to allow emergency exceptions to Idaho's abortion ban
item.description: The Supreme Court ruled in a case centered on Idaho's abortion ban and federal law that requires emergency rooms to give “stabilizing treatments."

item.title: Biden Campaign Announces $2M Debate Day Ad 'Blitz'
item.description: President Joe Biden's reelection campaign announced a seven-figure advertising "blitz" in battleground states and the city of Atlanta, Georgia, ahead of the first presidential debate on Thursday.

item.title: EXCLUSIVE SALE: 60% Off VIP Membership. 48 Hours ONLY!
Ad Wars: Trump and Biden campaigns take to airwaves and online ahead of and during presidential debate
item.description: While Biden and Trump meet on stage at the CNN Presidential Debate, their first face-to-face showdown in their 2024 election rematch, their campaigns will be engaged in combat in the ad wars.

item.title: Fred Fleitz to Newsmax: Europe's Migrant Problems Warning for US
item.description: Europe is becoming more conservative on the issue of unchecked migration, with the dire consequences serving as a warning for the United States, former Trump administration chief of staff of the National Security Council Fred Fleitz told Newsmax on Thursday.

item.title: Beginning of the End? New Poll Shows Trump Jumping Ahead of Biden As Debate Nears
Biden welcomes Bernie Sanders rallies boosting workers in swing state as Trump courts working class
item.description: President Biden's campaign is welcoming Sen. Bernie Sanders' choice to hold several rallies in swing state Wisconsin, where he performed significantly well in 2016, defeating Hillary Clinton in the Democratic primary.

item.title: Rep. Cammack to Newsmax: Trump Wins Debate by Showing Up
item.description: Rep. Kat Cammack, R-Fla., told Newsmax on Thursday that in Thursday night's presidential debate, all former President Donald Trump must do to come out on top is show up, despite the event being set to President Joe Biden's advantage.

item.title: Longtime Debate Co-Chairman Shreds CNN Format, Promises Comeback in 2028
New ad ties vulnerable Dem senator to Biden's 'failing' record ahead of CNN Presidential Debate
item.description: Ohio Democratic Sen. Sherrod Brown was hit with a new ad from his GOP opponent on Thursday, linking his record to that of President Biden's in a closely watching race.

item.title: Mitch McConnell: Biden a 'Good Guy'
item.description: President Joe Biden's policies, not his personality, should be what costs him the election, according to Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell, who calls him a "good guy," rather than following former President Donald Trump's "Crooked Joe" characterization of him.

item.title: North Carolina blocks RFK Jr., Cornel West from ballot – for now
item.description: The North Carolina elections board has delayed certification of We The People Party and Justice For All Party, which are planning to put RFK Jr. and Cornel West on the ballot respectively.

item.title: Report: Michelle Obama Frustrated With Biden Family
item.description: Former first lady Michelle Obama is upset with the Biden family for how it discarded her close friend Kathleen Buhle after her contentious divorce with Hunter Biden, Axios reported.
